text.tspan: Dr. C.J. Talimar is a scientist at our facility
who had a very bad accident involving a
subject who was very disobedient and
had to be put down. The subject lashed
out and ripped CJ's lower jaw off.
Fortunately, we found a replacement in
no time, and attached it where his lower
jaw was. He now communicates in morse
It's sort of devolved into a brassy sound
